        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/8559\">#8559</a> defines character module of a module. Character modules actually appear as an indexing set when proving enough-injectiveness of abelian groups but was not separated out as a definition back then. It is also useful in context of flatness, for modules are flat iff their character modules are injective, then using Baer, we relate ideals with flatness. </p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"224323\">@Junyan Xu</span> already started some preliminary reviews.</p>",
        "id": 405096592,
        "sender_full_name": "Jujian Zhang",
        "timestamp": 1701343528
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could you add the proof that (at least for R commutative), the category of R modules has enough injectives?</p>",
        "id": 405931694,
